Key Match Events: The Netherlands successfully chased Nepal's target of 107 runs, finishing at 108/4 in 18.4 overs.
Max O'Dowd led the scoring for the Netherlands with an unbeaten 54 runs off 48 balls, including 4 fours and 1 six.
Vikramjit Singh contributed 22 runs, Sybrand Engelbrecht added 14, and Bas de Leede remained not out with 11 runs.
For Nepal, Sompal Kami, Dipendra Singh Airee, and Abhinash Bohara each took a wicket.
Nepal scored 106 runs before being bowled out in 19.2 overs.
Captain Rohit Paudel top-scored for Nepal with 35 runs off 37 balls, hitting 5 fours.
Karan KC scored a quick 17 runs off 12 balls, including 2 sixes, and Gulsan Jha and Anil Shah added 11 runs each.
Tim Pringle and Logan Van Beek claimed 3 wickets each, while Paul Van Meekeren and Bas de Leede took 2 wickets apiece.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the first match for both teams in Group D of the competition.
Group D includes Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, and South Africa.
